name: Potion
rules: Heal 20 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: X Speed
rules: During this turn, the Retreat Cost of your Active Pokémon is 1 less.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Hand Scope
rules: Your opponent reveals their hand.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Pokédex
rules: Look at the top 3 cards of your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Poké Ball
rules: Put 1 random Basic Pokémon from your deck into your hand.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Red Card
rules: Your opponent shuffles their hand into their deck and draws 3 cards.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Professor's Research
rules: Draw 2 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Pokédex
rules: Look at the top 3 cards of your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Power Blast
attacks.text: Discard 2 Psychic Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.

name: Chansey
flavorText: This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

name: Meowth

attacks.name: Pay Day
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

name: Butterfree

abilities.name: Powder Heal
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.

flavorText: In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

name: Lapras ex
rules: ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

attacks.name: Bubble Drain
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Clefairy
flavorText: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

name: Mankey

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

name: Venusaur

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

name: Greninja

abilities.name: Water Shuriken
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may do 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

name: Haunter

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

name: Onix
flavorText: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

name: Jigglypuff

attacks.name: Sing
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

name: Bulbasaur
flavorText: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

name: Moltres ex
rules: ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

attacks.name: Inferno Dance
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. Take an amount of Fire Energy from your Energy Zone equal to the number of heads and attach it to your Benched Fire Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Snivy
flavorText: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

name: Volcarona

attacks.name: Volcanic Ash
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fire Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: Its burning body causes it to be unpopular in hot parts of the world, but in cold ones, Volcarona is revered as an embodiment of the sun.

name: Blastoise

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra Water Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

name: Eevee

attacks.name: Growl
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do −20 damage.

flavorText: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Cinccino

attacks.name: Do the Wave
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won't tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

name: Charmander

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

name: Piplup

attacks.name: Nap
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It doesn't like to be taken care of. It's difficult to bond with since it won't listen to its Trainer.

name: Turtwig
flavorText: It uses its whole body to photosynthesize when exposed to sunlight. Its shell is made from hardened soil.

name: Electivire

attacks.name: Exciting Voltage
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra Lightning Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

flavorText: The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.

name: Cresselia ex
rules: ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

abilities.name: Lunar Plumage
abilities.text: Whenever you attach a Psychic Energy from your Energy Zone to this Pokémon, heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Misdreavus

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: This Pokémon startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

name: Skarmory

attacks.name: Metal Arms
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 30 more damage.

flavorText: People fashion swords from Skarmory's shed feathers, so this Pokémon is a popular element in heraldic designs.

name: Chimchar
flavorText: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can't extinguish the fire.

name: Togepi
flavorText: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

name: Darkrai ex
rules: ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

abilities.name: Nightmare Aura
abilities.text: Whenever you attach a Darkness Energy from your Energy Zone to this Pokémon, do 20 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Cherrim

attacks.name: Leech Seed
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: After absorbing plenty of sunlight, Cherrim takes this form. It's full of energy while it's like this, and its liveliness will go on until sundown.

name: Raichu

abilities.name: Resilience Link
abilities.text: If you have Arceus or Arceus (TCG Pocket)|Arceus ex in play, this Pokémon takes −30 damage from attacks.

attacks.name: Spark
attacks.text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

name: Nosepass

attacks.name: Iron Defense
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

flavorText: It moves less than an inch a year, but when it's in a jam, it will spin and drill down into the ground in a split second.

name: Gible
flavorText: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

name: Staraptor

abilities.name: Defensive Whirlwind
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes −30 damage from attacks from Fighting Pokémon.

flavorText: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

name: Manaphy

attacks.name: Oceanic Gift
attacks.text: Choose 2 of your Benched Pokémon. For each of those Pokémon, take a Water Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to that Pokémon.

flavorText: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

name: Snorlax

attacks.name: Collapse
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

name: Mewtwo ex
rules: ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent gets 2 points.

attacks.name: Psydrive
attacks.text: Discard 2 Psychic Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Cyclizar

attacks.name: Overacceleration
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Overacceleration attack does +20 damage.

flavorText: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.

name: Sprigatito

attacks.name: Cry for Help
attacks.text: Put 1 random Grass Pokémon from your deck into your hand.

flavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

name: Floatzel

attacks.name: Attack the Wound
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has damage on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

name: Pawmot

abilities.name: Counterattack
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, do 20 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.

name: Machamp

attacks.name: Power Press
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra Fighting Energy attached, this attack does 50 more damage.

flavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

name: Ekans

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.

name: Bidoof
flavorText: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

name: Pachirisu

attacks.name: Plasma
attacks.text: Take a Lightning Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It's one of the kinds of Pokémon with electric cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.

name: Riolu
flavorText: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.
